That seems like a rather selfish and narrow thing to say.<p>I&#x27;ve always thought (ever since university) that code should take inspiration from math notation.<p>Instead of writing:<p><pre><code>    for (int i = 0; i < limit; i++) { acc += 1; }
</code></pre>
just write:<p><pre><code>    acc = ∑_(int i=0)^(limit);
</code></pre>
I think maybe one should do some more math before telling a world of mathematicians what to do. Besides, it&#x27;s <i>far</i> easier to create computer languages than the change math notation the world over.
